cantly improved. A simple $1/s^n$\ndependence for the continuum process can describe the measured cross sections,\nbut a better fit is obtained by an additional resonance near 4.2\\,GeV, which\ncould be an excited charmonium or a charmonium-like state.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Aug 2018 08:39:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 29 Aug 2018 17:31:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 16 May 2019 07:15:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-17"}
